    "The page mainly consists of three parts: the target repository path, LLM configuration, and flow control (for the orchestrator).",
    "Figure 9 displays the window that appears after clicking the \"Evaluate\" button.",
    "Since using an LLM as a judge is costly (consuming approximately 500 tokens per evaluation), this feature is optional in the web UI.",
    "Only when the user clicks the \"Evaluate\" button will the evaluation be triggered, after which the button changes to display the generated score.",
    "Cycles within the graph are detected using Tarjan's algorithm (Tarjan, 1972) and condensed into a single node."
